<br>
Ignorant people are so damn annoying.  People who are stuck in their old &quot;it worked for me, so it must be the right way to do things&quot; mentality annoy me. <br>
<br>
I just got back from lunch and was talking to the ladies in the office about my new pup.  The conversation veered toward leaving him at home, and I happily mentioned that my husband was able to go home for lunch so Ashton can eat lunch and go potty after being confined in his crate since 7:30 this morning.  He's a seven week old pup, and babies that young need to be fed three times a day.  They also can not be expected to wait 9 hours until they go potty.  Sorry, but it ain't gonna happen.  On that same note, it's much easier to go home to a clean pup than one who had no choice but to crap in his crate and lay in it.  <br>
<br>
Anyway, the ladies start giggling and shaking their heads at me.  I ask them what was so funny and they continue laughing until one of them sarcastically murmurs how they must have been a bad pet owner when they had dogs.  I tried to explain to them that he was too young to be expected to hold it all day, and that at his age, he needed three meals a day.  They just kept giggling and shaking their heads, all the while wearing a &quot;she's spoiling her dog&quot; expression.  <br>
<br>
It really hurt me (then angered me) to see their reactions to the way I am caring for my dog.  Nez isn't always going to go home at lunch...just until Ashton doesn't need three meals a day and can wait longer between potty breaks.<br>
<br>
Thanks for letting me use this as a way of silently screaming.  I'm just really perturbed at the level of ignorance some of the people of the older generations seem to dwell in.<br>
<br>
/sigh      <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.alinath.com/images/angel.gif " style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
